amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/24135459/cicilized-cycles-model-1-ebike-two-seater-carry-passenger-696x462.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/24135459/cicilized-cycles-model-1-ebike-two-seater-carry-passenger-1068x709.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/24135459/cicilized-cycles-model-1-ebike-two-seater-carry-passenger-632x420.jpg 632w\"></a></p><p>In fact, it immediately makes the aforementioned commuter ebikes look outdated. The Civilized Cycles founder, Zachary Schieffelin, seems to have thought of everything, producing the most practical bike for city dwellers on the market.</p><p>Having been a very successful Vespa dealer in the heart of NYC for many years, Zach knew he wanted to model his eBike on the moped. The step-thru frame and ability to carry an adult passenger are both features that were inspired by the Vespa, and of course Zach’s desire to create a functional vehicle that was actually a viable alternative to a car.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/24135417/cicilized-cycles-model-1-ebike-expandable-panniers.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/24135417/cicilized-cycles-model-1-ebike-expandable-panniers.jpg\" alt=\"cicilized cycles model 1 ebike expandable pannier bags\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/24135417/cicilized-cycles-model-1-ebike-expandable-panniers.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/24135417/cicilized-cycles-model-1-ebike-expandable-panniers-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/24135417/cicilized-cycles-model-1-ebike-expandable-panniers-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/24135417/cicilized-cycles-model-1-ebike-expandable-panniers-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/24135417/cicilized-cycles-model-1-ebike-expandable-panniers-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/24135417/cicilized-cycles-model-1-ebike-expandable-panniers-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/24135417/cicilized-cycles-model-1-ebike-expandable-panniers-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/24135417/cicilized-cycles-model-1-ebike-expandable-panniers-630x420.jpg 630w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb20 src ng ngcb20 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/24135417/cicilized-cycles-model-1-ebike-expandable-panniers.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/24135417/cicilized-cycles-model-1-ebike-expandable-panniers.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/24135417/cicilized-cycles-model-1-ebike-expandable-panniers-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/24135417/cicilized-cycles-model-1-ebike-expandable-panniers-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/24135417/cicilized-cycles-model-1-ebike-expandable-panniers-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/24135417/cicilized-cycles-model-1-ebike-expandable-panniers-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/24135417/cicilized-cycles-model-1-ebike-expandable-panniers-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/24135417/cicilized-cycles-model-1-ebike-expandable-panniers-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/24135417/cicilized-cycles-model-1-ebike-expandable-panniers-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a></p><p>The Model 1 blends the practicality of a cargo bike with the maneuverability of a regular eBike, thanks to its carefully designed expandable pannier bags. Unlike on most commuter bikes, these aren’t simply an add-on; they are a permanently integrated feature of the bike. A design team that normally does work for NASA and Nike helped develop these now-patented hard shell panniers said to be able to carry four fully loaded grocery bags.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/24135956/cicilized-cycles-model-1-ebike-single-pivot-rear-suspension.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/24135956/cicilized-cycles-model-1-ebike-single-pivot-rear-suspension.jpg\" alt=\"cicilized cycles model 1 ebike prototype suspension\" width=\"1200\" height=\"900\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/24135956/cicilized-cycles-model-1-ebike-single-pivot-rear-suspension.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/24135956/cicilized-cycles-model-1-ebike-single-pivot-rear-suspension-297x223.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/24135956/cicilized-cycles-model-1-ebike-single-pivot-rear-suspension-800x600.jpg 800w,