p-content/uploads/2021/06/24135440/cicilized-cycles-model-1-ebike-smart-headlamp-120x82.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/24135440/cicilized-cycles-model-1-ebike-smart-headlamp-768x527.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/24135440/cicilized-cycles-model-1-ebike-smart-headlamp-218x150.jpg 218w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/24135440/cicilized-cycles-model-1-ebike-smart-headlamp-696x478.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/24135440/cicilized-cycles-model-1-ebike-smart-headlamp-1068x733.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/24135440/cicilized-cycles-model-1-ebike-smart-headlamp-612x420.jpg 612w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/24135440/cicilized-cycles-model-1-ebike-smart-headlamp-100x70.jpg 100w\"></a></p><p>The Civilized Cycles Model 1 features integrated lights. The head lamp is courteous to other road users in that it automatically dips its high beam when it detects and oncoming vehicle’s head lights. In addition to the usual rear light, there’s a also a rear brake light alerting anyone behind you that you’re slowing down.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/24135423/cicilized-cycles-model-1-ebike-integrated-tailight-braking.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/24135423/cicilized-cycles-model-1-ebike-integrated-tailight-braking.jpg\" alt=\"cicilized cycles model 1 ebike tail light\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/24135423/cicilized-cycl